{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1cc91f79-901f-4b8f-a037-8edb9dd089c7","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n```bash\ndotnet --version          # verify SDK 11.0.100+ is installed\ndotnet restore            # pull updated packages\ndotnet build              # confirm it compiles\ndotnet test               # run tests\n```\n\nAlso check your NuGet packages — any `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*` packages should be bumped to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dbfa9981-c2d3-493d-a206-cc63abc26271","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search their codebase since they've described the files involved.","outputTokens":307,"requestId":"300E:271D55:1605FC8:18CD6FD:6A067BA0"},"id":"2cc88f97-99ba-4af7-bd14-88be59fef9b8","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:49:26.691Z","parentId":"5be5a5f9-84f0-4558-9a7c-e327f78abd06"}
